description: The Han River, also known as the Han River, is a major river on the Korean Peninsula and the fourth longest river on the Korean Peninsula, after the Yalu River, Tumen River and Nakdong River.

A modern bridge on the Han River, it is a bridge connecting Hanjiang Road, Yongshan District and Bendong, Dongjak District, with a width of 36.8 meters and a length of 1005 meters. It is an earlier bridge across the Han River on the Han River Island. It used to be called Hanjiang Highway Bridge before, but on November 7, 1984, the bridge name was changed to Hanjiang Bridge in order to be consistent with the road name Hanjiang Road.
